HEADWORD: Reversioner
<hw>Re*ver"sion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One who has a reversion, or who is entitled to lands or tenements,
after a particular estate granted is terminated.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

